{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1116,"text":"What stands between Africa's current\nprostrate condition"},{"time":5251,"text":"and a future of prosperity and abundance\nfor its long-suffering populations?"},{"time":10912,"text":"One word:"},{"time":12725,"text":"knowledge."},{"time":14798,"text":"If Africa is to become a continent\nthat offers the best life for humans,"},{"time":19340,"text":"it must become a knowledge society"},{"time":22322,"text":"immediately."},{"time":23994,"text":"This is what I have called\n\"Africa's knowledge imperative.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":29923,"text":"Our universities must reduce emphasis\non producing manpower"},{"time":33778,"text":"for running our civil society,"},{"time":36333,"text":"our economy"},{"time":38123,"text":"and our political institutions."},{"time":41148,"text":"They should be dedicated mainly\nto knowledge production."},{"time":46114,"text":"What sense is there\nin producing civil engineers"},{"time":50068,"text":"who are not supported\nby soil scientists and geologists,"},{"time":53719,"text":"who make it their business\nto create knowledge about our soil"},{"time":58031,"text":"and our rocks?"},{"time":60417,"text":"What use is there in producing lawyers"},{"time":63660,"text":"without juries who produce knowledge"},{"time":68447,"text":"of the underlying philosophical\nfoundations of the legal system?"},{"time":73642,"text":"We must seek knowledge."},{"time":76466,"text":"We must approach the matter of knowledge"},{"time":79556,"text":"with a maniacal commitment,"},{"time":82445,"text":"without let or hindrance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85480,"text":"Though we must seek knowledge\nto solve problems we know of,"},{"time":89860,"text":"we must also seek knowledge"},{"time":92140,"text":"when there is no problem in view --"},{"time":94849,"text":"especially when there\nis no problem in view."},{"time":99263,"text":"We must seek to know as much\nof what there is to know of all things,"},{"time":104439,"text":"limited only by the insufficiency\nof our human nature,"},{"time":108742,"text":"and not only when the need arises."},{"time":112534,"text":"Those who do not seek knowledge\nwhen it is not needed"},{"time":117561,"text":"will not have it when they must have it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122777,"text":"The biggest crisis in Africa today\nis the crisis of knowledge:"},{"time":126896,"text":"how to produce it,"},{"time":128940,"text":"how to manage it,"},{"time":130595,"text":"and how to deploy it effectively."},{"time":134421,"text":"For instance, Africa does not\nhave a water crisis."},{"time":139284,"text":"It has a knowledge crisis\nregarding its water,"},{"time":143251,"text":"where and what types it is,"},{"time":145762,"text":"how it can be tapped and made available\nwhere and when needed to all and sundry."},{"time":153144,"text":"How does a continent that is home"},{"time":155827,"text":"to some of the largest\nbodies of water in the world --"},{"time":159708,"text":"the Nile,"},{"time":161587,"text":"the Niger,"},{"time":163291,"text":"the Congo,"},{"time":164700,"text":"the Zambezi"},{"time":166274,"text":"and the Orange Rivers --"},{"time":168553,"text":"be said to have a water crisis,"},{"time":171020,"text":"including in countries"},{"time":173091,"text":"where those rivers are?"},{"time":176387,"text":"And that is only surface water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179045,"text":"While we wrongly dissipate our energies\nfighting the wrong crises,"},{"time":183030,"text":"all those who invest in knowledge about us"},{"time":185736,"text":"are busy figuring out\nhow to pipe water from Libya's aquifers"},{"time":191458,"text":"to quench Europe's thirst."},{"time":194811,"text":"Such is our knowledge\nof our water resources"},{"time":197208,"text":"that many of our countries have given up"},{"time":199364,"text":"on making potable water a routine presence"},{"time":202125,"text":"in the lives of Africans,"},{"time":203908,"text":"rich or poor,"},{"time":205587,"text":"high and low,"},{"time":207066,"text":"rural and urban."},{"time":209252,"text":"We eagerly accept\nwhat the merchants of misery"},{"time":212746,"text":"and the global African Studies\nsafari professoriat"},{"time":216293,"text":"and their aid-addled,"},{"time":218273,"text":"autonomy-fearing African minions"},{"time":221146,"text":"in government, universities\nand civil society"},{"time":224408,"text":"tell us regarding how nature\nhas been to stinting towards Africa"},{"time":228568,"text":"when it comes to the distribution\nof water resources in the world."},{"time":232947,"text":"We are content to run our cities\nand rural dwellings alike"},{"time":236727,"text":"on boreholes."},{"time":240213,"text":"How does one run metropolises\non boreholes and wells?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":247055,"text":"Does Africa have a food crisis?"},{"time":249861,"text":"Again, the answer is no."},{"time":253429,"text":"It is yet another knowledge crisis\nregarding Africa's agricultural resources,"},{"time":258680,"text":"what and where they are,"},{"time":260724,"text":"and how they can be best managed\nto make Africans live more lives"},{"time":265261,"text":"that are worth living."},{"time":267907,"text":"Otherwise, how does one explain the fact"},{"time":270279,"text":"that geography puts the source\nof the River Nile in Ethiopia,"},{"time":274572,"text":"and its people cannot\nhave water for their lives?"},{"time":278736,"text":"And the same geography\nputs California in the desert,"},{"time":282641,"text":"but it is a breadbasket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285578,"text":"The difference, obviously,\nis not geography."},{"time":289413,"text":"It is knowledge."},{"time":291686,"text":"Colorado's aquifers"},{"time":293702,"text":"grow California's pistachios."},{"time":296900,"text":"Why can't Libya's aquifers"},{"time":299102,"text":"grow sorghum in northern Nigeria?"},{"time":302882,"text":"Why does Nigeria not aspire"},{"time":305739,"text":"to feed the world,"},{"time":307866,"text":"not just itself?"},{"time":309797,"text":"If Africa's land is so poor,\nas we are often told,"},{"time":313652,"text":"why are outsiders,"},{"time":315884,"text":"from the United Arab Emirates\nall the way to South Korea,"},{"time":320073,"text":"buying up vast acreages of our land,"},{"time":323349,"text":"to grow food, no less,"},{"time":325541,"text":"to feed their people"},{"time":327262,"text":"in lands that are truly more\ngeographically stinting?"},{"time":331958,"text":"The new landowners are not planning\nto import new topsoil"},{"time":335320,"text":"to make their African\nacquisitions more arable."},{"time":338246,"text":"Again, a singular instance\nof knowledge deficiency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344990,"text":"In the 19th century,"},{"time":347430,"text":"our predecessors,"},{"time":348914,"text":"just years removed from the ravages\nof slavery and the slave trade,"},{"time":353837,"text":"were exploring the Niger and Congo Rivers"},{"time":357052,"text":"with a view to turning Africa's resources\nto the advantage of its people"},{"time":361125,"text":"and to the rest of humanity,"},{"time":363513,"text":"and their 20th-century successors\nwere dreaming of harnessing"},{"time":367640,"text":"the powers of the River Congo"},{"time":369872,"text":"to light up the whole continent."},{"time":372642,"text":"Now only buccaneer capitalists from Europe"},{"time":376102,"text":"are scheming of doing the same,"},{"time":378502,"text":"but for exports to Europe\nand South Africa."},{"time":382736,"text":"And they are even suggesting"},{"time":384404,"text":"that Congolese may not\nbenefit from this scheme,"},{"time":387014,"text":"because, according to them,\nCongolese communities are too small"},{"time":391029,"text":"to make providing them with electricity"},{"time":394123,"text":"a viable concern."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398174,"text":"The solution?"},{"time":399977,"text":"Africa must become a knowledge society,"},{"time":402945,"text":"a defining characteristic\nof the modern age."},{"time":406866,"text":"We neither are, nor are we\non the path to becoming,"},{"time":412199,"text":"a knowledge society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415010,"text":"Things have not always been this way"},{"time":418696,"text":"when it comes to knowledge\nproduction and Africa."},{"time":421655,"text":"In antiquity, the world went to Africa\nfor intellectual enrichment."},{"time":427339,"text":"There were celebrated centers of learning,"},{"time":430482,"text":"attracting questers from all parts\nof the then-known world,"},{"time":434586,"text":"seeking knowledge about that world."},{"time":437804,"text":"What happened then\nhas implications for our present."},{"time":441968,"text":"For example,"},{"time":443810,"text":"how Roman Africa managed the relationship\nbetween settlers and natives"},{"time":450500,"text":"between the second and fourth\ncenturies of our era"},{"time":454116,"text":"might have something to teach us\nwhen it comes to confronting"},{"time":457132,"text":"not-too-dissimilar problems\nat the present time."},{"time":461345,"text":"But how many classics departments\ndo we have in our universities?"},{"time":466423,"text":"Because we do not invest in knowledge,"},{"time":468970,"text":"people come to Africa now"},{"time":471051,"text":"not as a place of intellectual enrichment,"},{"time":474171,"text":"but as a place where they sate\ntheir thirst for exotica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480538,"text":"Yet for the last half-millennium,"},{"time":483544,"text":"Africa has been hemorrhaging\nand exporting knowledge"},{"time":487057,"text":"to the rest of the world."},{"time":489273,"text":"Regardless of the popular description\nof it as a trade in bodies,"},{"time":493986,"text":"the European trans-Atlantic\nslave trade and slavery"},{"time":497787,"text":"was one of the most radical\nand longest programs"},{"time":501232,"text":"of African brains export in history."},{"time":504831,"text":"American slave owners may have pretended\nthat Africans were mere brutes,"},{"time":509929,"text":"beasts of burden,"},{"time":511597,"text":"almost as inert and dumb\nas other farm implements"},{"time":515566,"text":"they classified them with\nin their ledgers."},{"time":519052,"text":"And that's what they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521099,"text":"The enslaved Africans, on the other hand,"},{"time":523563,"text":"knew their were embodiments of knowledge."},{"time":526659,"text":"They were smiths, they were poets,"},{"time":529223,"text":"they were political counselors,\nthey were princes and princesses,"},{"time":532570,"text":"they were mythologists,\nthey were herbologists,"},{"time":537689,"text":"they were chefs."},{"time":539206,"text":"The list is endless."},{"time":541367,"text":"They, to take a single example,"},{"time":543885,"text":"brought the knowledge of rice cultivation"},{"time":546905,"text":"to the American South."},{"time":550101,"text":"They created some of the most\noriginal civilizational elements"},{"time":554600,"text":"for which the United States\nis now celebrated."},{"time":558237,"text":"They deployed their knowledge,\nfor the most part,"},{"time":561361,"text":"without compensation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563867,"text":"For the last half-millennium,\nbeginning with the slave trade,"},{"time":567399,"text":"Africa has been exporting brains"},{"time":570069,"text":"while simultaneously breaking\nthe chains of knowledge transmission"},{"time":574815,"text":"on the continent itself,"},{"time":576569,"text":"with dire consequences for the systems\nof knowledge production in Africa."},{"time":581664,"text":"Successive generations are cut off\nfrom the intellectual production"},{"time":586258,"text":"of their predecessors."},{"time":588363,"text":"We keep producing for external markets"},{"time":591430,"text":"while beggaring our own internal needs."},{"time":595411,"text":"At present,"},{"time":596763,"text":"much of the best knowledge about Africa"},{"time":599390,"text":"is neither produced nor housed there,"},{"time":602722,"text":"even when it is produced by Africans."},{"time":606634,"text":"Because we are dominated\nby immediate needs"},{"time":609119,"text":"and relevant solutions when it comes\nto what we should know,"},{"time":612650,"text":"we are happy to hand over to others"},{"time":615199,"text":"the responsibility to produce knowledge,"},{"time":617683,"text":"including knowledge about, of and for us,"},{"time":621985,"text":"and to do so far away from us."},{"time":624853,"text":"We are ever eager to consume knowledge"},{"time":628020,"text":"and have but a mere portion of it"},{"time":630443,"text":"without any anxiety about\nownership and location."},{"time":635707,"text":"African universities\nare now all too content"},{"time":639334,"text":"to have e-connections\nwith libraries elsewhere,"},{"time":642884,"text":"having given up ambitions\non building libraries"},{"time":645782,"text":"to which the world would come\nfor intellectual edification."},{"time":650411,"text":"Control over who decides\nwhat should be stocked on our shelves"},{"time":654633,"text":"and how access to collections\nshould be determined"},{"time":658297,"text":"are made to rest on our trust\nin our partners' good faith"},{"time":662152,"text":"that they will not abandon us\ndown the road."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665981,"text":"This must change."},{"time":669093,"text":"Africa must become\na place of knowledge again."},{"time":673433,"text":"Knowledge production\nactually expands the economy."},{"time":679262,"text":"Take archaeological digs, for instance,"},{"time":682361,"text":"and their impact on tourism."},{"time":685527,"text":"Our desires to unearth our antiquity,"},{"time":688931,"text":"especially those remote times\nof which we have no written records,"},{"time":693728,"text":"requires investment in archaeology\nand related disciplines,"},{"time":698766,"text":"e.g., paleoanthropology."},{"time":701715,"text":"Yet, although it is our past\nwe seek to know,"},{"time":705557,"text":"by sheer serendipity,"},{"time":707935,"text":"archaeology may shed light\non the global human experience"},{"time":711824,"text":"and yield economic payoffs"},{"time":714011,"text":"that were no part\nof the original reasons for digging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718969,"text":"We must find a way to make knowledge\nand its production sexy and rewarding;"},{"time":725985,"text":"rewarding, not in the crass\nsense of moneymaking"},{"time":729600,"text":"but in terms of making it worthwhile\nto indulge in the pursuit of knowledge,"},{"time":735101,"text":"support the existence"},{"time":736519,"text":"of knowledge-producing\ngroups and intellectuals,"},{"time":739720,"text":"ensuring that the continent"},{"time":743499,"text":"becomes the immediate locus\nof knowledge production,"},{"time":746729,"text":"distribution and consumption,"},{"time":749385,"text":"and that instead of having\nits depositories"},{"time":751904,"text":"beyond Africa's boundaries,"},{"time":753921,"text":"people once more come\nfrom the rest of the world,"},{"time":757706,"text":"even if in virtual space,\nto learn from us."},{"time":762037,"text":"All this we do as custodians\non behalf of common humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770157,"text":"Creating a knowledge society in Africa,"},{"time":773501,"text":"for me, would be one way to celebrate\nand simultaneously enhance diversity"},{"time":779454,"text":"by infinitely enriching it with material\nand additional artifacts --"},{"time":784887,"text":"artifacts that we furnish"},{"time":787020,"text":"by our strivings"},{"time":789019,"text":"in the knowledge field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791047,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792477,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}